    "source_sections": {
      "references": "",
      "remarks": "Asked by Erd\\H{o}s and Straus. \nFor example when $n=2$ we have $k=5$:\\[2\\times 3 \\times 4 \\times 5\\times 6 \\mid 7 \\times 8 \\times 9\\times 10\\times 11.\\]and when $n=3$ we have $k=4$:\\[3\\times 4\\times 5\\times 6 \\mid 7\\times 8\\times 9\\times 10.\\]Bhavik Mehta has computed the minimal such $k$ for $1\\leq n\\leq 18$ (now available as A375071 on the OEIS)."
    },
